style.
  .owl-theme .owl-nav.disabled+.owl-dots {
    margin-top: -25px;
    z-index: 11;
    position: relative;
  }

  .owl-dots span {
    border: 1px solid #909090;
  }
  .owl-item{
    z-index: 10; /* Fix for OwlCarousel2 Issue #772 (loop flicker) */
  }
script(type='text/javascript').
  $( document ).ready(function() {
    $("#owl-demo").width($(window).width());
    $('body > .container').css('position', 'static')
    $("#owl-demo").owlCarousel({
      items: 1,
      loop: true,
      margin: 10,
      autoplay: true,
      autoplayTimeout: 5000,
      autoplayHoverPause: true,
      dots: true
    });
    var owl = $("#owl-demo").data('owlCarousel');
    $(window).resize(function() {
      $("#owl-demo").width($(window).width());
    });
  });
.intro(style="margin-top: 360px;")
  div.first
    div.shariff(data-lang="en", data-services='["facebook", "googleplus", "twitter", "whatsapp", "reddit"]', data-backend-url="//pimatic.org/shariff-backend/" )
    h2 pimatic 
    :markdown
      is a home automation framework that runs on [node.js](http://nodejs.org). It provides a 
      common extensible platform for home control and automation tasks.  
  div.row
    div.col-lg-6
      h4
        span.glyphicon.glyphicon-list-alt
        |  Uniform interface
      :markdown
        It defines several schemata for different home devices and sensors, so that all devices can be 
        controled uniform and are presented in a common interface.
    div.col-lg-6
      h4
        span.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok
        |  Automation by rules
      :markdown
        Automation tasks can be defined by rules in the form of "if this then that", where the "this" and 
        the "that" part can be fully custemized by plugins. See [the rule page](/guide/usage/rules) for 
        more details.
    div.col-lg-6
      h4
        span.glyphicon.glyphicon-phone
        |  Web-based
      :markdown
        The mobile frontend plugin provides a nice web frontend with a sensor overview, device control and
        rule definition. The web interface is build using [express](http://expressjs.com) and 
        [jQuery Mobile](http://jquerymobile.comâ€Ž).
    div.col-lg-6
      h4
        span.glyphicon.glyphicon-plus
        |  Extensible
      :markdown
        pimatic is extensible by various plugins adding features and integrating existing hardware and software.
